British Airways (BA) has opened its new lounge in O.R. Tambo International Airport. The lounge has undergone significant refurbishment with the new and improved space being converted into one large lounge with a dedicated boutique dining area for First customers. BA said that the carefully curated lounge follows a new design concept for the airline, which debuted in 2018, and features the very best of British and South African design “The 880 square metre lounge can host up to 247 customers and offers a modern lobby bar area for socialising, a brasserie dining area and office space with ample work stations with power outlets,” it said. “A peaceful, separate seating area with a mix of elegant armchairs and banquette seating is available for those who wish to recharge ahead of their journey with complimentary magazines and newspapers.” It added that zoned areas in the lounge will enable guests to choose what area they would like to relax in depending on their mood, with a music system and bespoke playlist. <img class="size-full wp-image-353435 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/britishairways_216861052576567.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="853" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/britishairways_216861052576567.jpg 1280w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/britishairways_216861052576567-300x200.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/britishairways_216861052576567-768x512.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/britishairways_216861052576567-1024x682.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/britishairways_216861052576567-1200x800.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" />
